President Joe Biden has ordered that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff as a sign of respect for the victims of the attack at the United States Capitol on April 2. This order applies to the White House, public buildings and grounds, military posts and naval stations, and naval vessels of the Federal Government in the District of Columbia and throughout the United States and its Territories and possessions until sunset on April 6. The flag will also be flown at half-staff at all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations. This order was signed by President Biden on April 2, 2021.